Database Migrations — GuruPix (Alembic)

GuruPix uses Alembic for all Postgres schema migrations. The database URL
is read from app.core.config.Settings (which loads from .env / env vars).

Current schema (001_initial_schema):
  - users, oauth_accounts    (Auth)
  - profiles                 (User preferences)
  - items                    (Catalog: movies/series/episodes)
  - item_availability        (Where to watch)
  - item_reviews_agg         (Review signals)
  - events                   (Learning loop / feedback)
  - models                   (Model registry)
  - contexts, context_events (Contextual "vibes" prompting)

Prerequisites:
  - Postgres running (start with: make docker_up  OR  docker_restart)
  - Backend venv activated

Commands (run from backend/):
  alembic upgrade head                            # Apply all migrations
  alembic downgrade base                          # Drop all tables
  alembic revision -m "description" --autogenerate  # Generate migration from model changes
  alembic downgrade -1                            # Roll back one revision
  alembic history                                 # Show revision history
  alembic current                                 # Show current revision

Testing:
  make test                     # Runs all tests (starts Docker, runs migrations automatically)
  make test-backend-integration # Runs integration tests only (includes migration + smoke tests)

  The integration test suite (tests/integration/test_db_migrations.py) verifies:
    1. alembic upgrade head applies cleanly from an empty database
    2. upgrade head is idempotent (running it twice doesn't fail)
    3. Insert/select/delete smoke test for every table

Files:
  alembic.ini                  — Alembic config (points to this directory)
  migrations/env.py            — Loads Settings, sets sync DB URL, imports all models
  migrations/script.py.mako    — Template for new migration files
  migrations/versions/         — Migration scripts (001_initial_schema.py, ...)
